1.Version check -> git --Version

2.Configure Username -> git config --global user.name "Name"

3.Configure Email -> git config --global user.email "mail@gmail.com"

4.Verify Configuration -> git config --global --list

5.Configure Notepad ++ as Default Editor -> git config --global core.editor "notepad++"

6.Create Repository -> git init GitDemo  (to Move) -> cd GitDemo

7.Check Hidden Files -> ls -al

8.create welcome.txt -> echo "Welcome to the version control" > welcome.txt

9.Verify file -> ls -al;

10. Display File -> welcome.txt

11.Check Staus -> git Status

12.Stage File -> git add welcome.txt

13.Commit -> git commit -m "Update"

14.git Status

15.git remote add origin "Git gub Link"

16.Pull Request -> git pull origin master

17.Push Request -> git push -u origin main